A Unified Quantum Computing Simulator
Vision
Quantum computing has seen exponential growth, with multiple frameworks such as Qiskit(IBM), Cirq(google), and pennylane(blackbird-Xanadu) leading the way. However, a significant challenge remains: the fragmentation of tools makes it difficult for researchers and developers to work seamlessly across different platforms. QuantumFlow aims to bridge this gap by providing an intuitive, drag-and-drop interface for quantum circuit design, measurement, and visualization. This open-source project will foster collaboration, enable a unified approach to quantum computing, and support fundamental tasks.



